cs.IT, cs.FM, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with LDPC codes, which are a popular topic in information theory. 
- cs.FM (Formal Methods) is also likely as the paper provides precise conditions for high girth in the Tanner graph of the codes, which can be seen as a formal method. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is a possibility as LDPC codes are used in various communication systems, including wireless networks. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possibility as LDPC codes are used in coding for distributed storage systems, which can be seen as a social network of storage nodes. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possibility as the paper proposes a new class of LDPC codes, which can be seen as a new data structure.
